-- UBS Hires Mittelman of Lime Brokerage to Develop Stock Trading Strategies
-- Nina Mehta
-- 2010-06-25T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/ubs-hires-mittelman-of-lime-brokerage-to-develop-stock-trading-strategies.html

          
          
             UBS AG  hired Debbie Mittelman of
Lime Brokerage Holdings LLC to develop and manage electronic
stock-trading products, according to an internal memo sent to
employees today.  
 She will report to  Charles Susi , head of direct execution
services for the Americas, and be based in New York and
Stamford, Connecticut, the memo said. Her title will be global
head of direct execution product management, according to the
memo, which was confirmed by UBS spokeswoman  Kelly Smith .
She’ll be responsible for the broker’s platform for trade
analytics and for a system customers can use to execute orders.  
 Mittelman was director of product for U.S. equities at New
York-based Lime, where she specialized in automated and high-
volume electronic trading strategies, the memo said. She has
also worked at Instinet Group Inc. and Goldman Sachs Group Inc.
and has a master’s degree in business administration from
Columbia University, the memo said.  
